'''Pablo Martín Páez Gavira'''{{efn|{{IPA|es|ˈpaβlo maɾˈtim ˈpaeθ ɣaˈβiɾa}};<ref>In isolation, ''Martín'' and ''Gavira'' are pronounced {{IPA|es|maɾˈtin|}} and {{IPA|es|ɡaˈβiɾa|}} respectively.</ref>}} (born 5 August 2004), known as '''Gavi''',{{efn|{{IPA|es|ˈɡaβi|pron}}}} is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{Spanish football updater|Barcelona}} club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

== Early life ==
Gavi was born in [[Los Palacios y Villafranca]], [[Sevilla Province|Sevilla]], [[Andalusia]].<ref name="WF" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/barcelona/2021/09/06/613217d8e2704e391a8b4580.html |title="El equipo de Gavi" |trans-title="Gavi's Team" |first=Cristina |last=Navarro |date=6 September 2021 |accessdate=3 August 2022 |newspaper=Marca |language=Spanish |archive-date=2 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220802233214/https://www.marca.com/futbol/barcelona/2021/09/06/613217d8e2704e391a8b4580.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Gavi started his career at La Liara Balompié, a club in his hometown, where he spent two years, between 2010 and 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://inews.co.uk/sport/football/gavi-fc-barcelona-youngster-undone-laces-born-big-stage-la-liara-balompie-1340007 |title=Gavi: The FC Barcelona youngster with undone laces who was 'born' for the big stage |first=Simon |last=Hart |date=8 December 2021 |accessdate=3 August 2022 |website=inews.co.uk |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922075524/https://inews.co.uk/sport/football/gavi-fc-barcelona-youngster-undone-laces-born-big-stage-la-liara-balompie-1340007 |url-status=live }}</ref> From there he moved on to [[Real Betis]]'s [[youth academy]], where he spent two [[football season|seasons]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.estadiodeportivo.com/futbol-sevillano/2021/10/07/liara-reivindica-gavi-oliver-atom/358663.html |title=La Liara reivindica a Gavi: "Era Oliver Atom" |trans-title=La Liara vindicates Gavi: "He was Oliver Atom" |date=8 October 2021 |access-date=8 October 2021 |first=Rafael |last=Cala |website=estadiodeportivo.com |language=Spanish |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922130704/https://www.estadiodeportivo.com/futbol-sevillano/2021/10/07/liara-reivindica-gavi-oliver-atom/358663.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2606115/a-special-fixture-for-gavi |title=A special fixture for Gavi |date=6 May 2022 |accessdate=3 August 2022 |publisher=FC Barcelona |archive-date=3 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003104432/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2606115/a-special-fixture-for-gavi |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored 95 goals for the youth team of [[Real Betis]].<ref name=vavel>{{cite web |url=https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/2018/12/02/fc-barcelona/958530-gavi-el-maestro-delgol.html |title=Gavi, el maestro de La Masía |trans-title=Gavi, the maestro of La Masía |first=Alicia |last=Navarro |date=4 December 2018 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=vavel.com |language=Spanish |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092351/https://www.vavel.com/es/futbol/2018/12/02/fc-barcelona/958530-gavi-el-maestro-delgol.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Barcelona===
====Youth career====
In 2015, at the age of 11, he signed for [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2021/07/30/fc-barcelona-preseason-has-seen-coach-ronald-koeman-find-new-golden-boys/?sh=6599bcd2a2ab |title=FC Barcelona Preseason Has Seen Coach Ronald Koeman Find New 'Golden Boys' |first=Tom |last=Sanderson |date=30 July 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=forbes.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092344/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2021/07/30/fc-barcelona-preseason-has-seen-coach-ronald-koeman-find-new-golden-boys/?sh=6599bcd2a2ab |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/43c43d29-7517-4d8b-8cfb-153fa6a929fd/ |title=Scouting report on Pablo Paez 'Gavi' - the little maestro from La Masia |first=Jacek |last=Kulig |date=19 May 2020 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=tribuna.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092400/https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/43c43d29-7517-4d8b-8cfb-153fa6a929fd/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In September 2020, he signed his first professional contract with the Catalan club, and was promoted directly from the under-16 team to the under-19 team.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sport.es/en/news/futbol-base/young-star-gavi-signs-new-contract-with-barcelona-8103335 |title=Young star Gavi signs new contract with Barcelona |date=7 September 2020 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=sport.es |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092407/https://www.sport.es/en/news/futbol-base/young-star-gavi-signs-new-contract-with-barcelona-8103335 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/gavi-la-masia-wonderkid-future-barcelona-midfield/1niafhrm9q3wc18s9n7c2zwb9i |title=Gavi: La Masia wonderkid set to be the future of Barcelona's midfield |first=Adrià |last=Soldevila |date=3 June 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=goal.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092808/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/gavi-la-masia-wonderkid-future-barcelona-midfield/1niafhrm9q3wc18s9n7c2zwb9i |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut for [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]] on 21 February 2021, in the 6–0 home routing of [[CE L'Hospitalet|L'Hospitalet]], coming on as a substitute for [[Nico González (footballer, born 2002)|Nico González]] in the 77th minute.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/news/2040540/gavi-becomes-14th-under-19s-player-to-debut-for-barca-b-under-garcia-pimienta |title=Gavi becomes 14th Under-19s player to debut for Barça B under Garcia Pimienta |date=22 February 2021 |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=24 November 2021 |archive-date=4 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304012804/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/barca-b/news/2040540/gavi-becomes-14th-under-19s-player-to-debut-for-barca-b-under-garcia-pimienta |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his first start for Barça B the following 14 March in a 1–0 [[Derbi barceloní|derby]] win against [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] at the [[Ciutat Esportiva Dani Jarque]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol-base/fiesta-juvenil-barca-b-hunde-11578356 |title=La fiesta 'juvenil' del Barça B hunde al RCD Espanyol B |first=Albert |last=Rogé |date=14 March 2021 |accessdate=24 November 2021 |website=sport.es |language=Spanish |archive-date=24 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124024947/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol-base/fiesta-juvenil-barca-b-hunde-11578356 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
Having featured twice for [[FC Barcelona B|Barcelona B]] in the [[2020–21 Segunda División B|2020–21]] season, Gavi was promoted to the senior squad for pre-season friendlies with the first team ahead of the start of the [[2021–22 FC Barcelona season|new season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-kw/news/gavi-demir-barcelona-wonderkids-impressing-koeman-pre-season/b1eg4f939dz21lpndiuc9bhmj |title=Gavi, Demir & the Barcelona wonderkids impressing Koeman in pre-season |first=Rik |last=Sharma |date=2 August 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=goal.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092343/https://www.goal.com/en-kw/news/gavi-demir-barcelona-wonderkids-impressing-koeman-pre-season/b1eg4f939dz21lpndiuc9bhmj |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/gavi-puro-arte-duende-11918125 |title=Gavi, puro arte y mucho duende |first=German |last=Bona |date=17 July 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=sport.es |language=Spanish |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092348/https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/gavi-puro-arte-duende-11918125 |url-status=live }}</ref> After good performances in wins against [[Gimnàstic de Tarragona]] and [[Girona FC|Girona]], Gavi was reported to have pushed ahead of [[Riqui Puig]] in manager [[Ronald Koeman]]'s squad selection.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/cantera/20210722/410632393099/gavi-se-crecio-entre-los-mayores-en-su-debut.html |title=Gavi se creció entre los mayores en su debut |first=Ferran |last=Martínez |date=22 July 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=mundodeportivo.com |language=Spanish |archive-date=22 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210722213102/https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/cantera/20210722/410632393099/gavi-se-crecio-entre-los-mayores-en-su-debut.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://heavy.com/sports/fc-barcelona/koeman-prefers-barcelona-teen-to-riqui-puig-report/ |title=Koeman Prefers Barcelona Teen To Riqui Puig: Report |first=Gill |last=Clark |date=27 July 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=heavy.com |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828135030/https://heavy.com/sports/fc-barcelona/koeman-prefers-barcelona-teen-to-riqui-puig-report/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He continued this good run of form in a 3–0 win against German opposition [[VfB Stuttgart]], earning comparisons with Barcelona legend [[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/2021-08-01-16yearold-barca-kid-gavi-stuns-fans-with-fantastic-performance-gets-compared-to-xavi/ |title=16-year-old Barca kid Gavi stuns fans with fantastic performance, gets compared to Xavi |first=Kosta |last=König |date=2 August 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=tribuna.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092347/https://tribuna.com/en/news/2021-08-01-16yearold-barca-kid-gavi-stuns-fans-with-fantastic-performance-gets-compared-to-xavi/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/trending/gavi-a-delicate-touch-that-showed-he-may-well-be-barcelonas-new-xavi/ |title=Gavi & a delicate touch that showed he could well be Barcelona's new Xavi |first=Joshua |last=Law |date=2 August 2021 |accessdate=2 August 2021 |website=planetfootball.com |archive-date=2 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210802092353/https://www.planetfootball.com/trending/gavi-a-delicate-touch-that-showed-he-may-well-be-barcelonas-new-xavi/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 29 August 2021, he played his first official match for Barcelona's first team in the 2–1 [[La Liga]] win over [[Getafe CF|Getafe]], replacing [[Sergi Roberto]] in the 73rd minute. On 18 December, he scored his first goal for the club and provided an assist in the 3–2 home win over [[Elche CF|Elche]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2421309/first-goals-for-gavi-and-jutgla |title=First goals for Gavi and Jutglà |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=18 December 2021 |accessdate=19 December 2021 |archive-date=19 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219060434/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2421309/first-goals-for-gavi-and-jutgla |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2022–23 season====
On 15 January 2023, Gavi scored a goal and provided two assists to be named man of the match in a 3–1 victory over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2023 Supercopa de España Final|Supercopa de España Final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jan/15/gavi-helps-barcelona-ease-past-real-madrid-to-win-spanish-super-cup |title=Barcelona ease past Real Madrid to win Spanish Super Cup as PSG lose again |work=The Guardian |date=15 January 2023 |access-date=16 January 2023 |archive-date=15 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230115214433/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jan/15/gavi-helps-barcelona-ease-past-real-madrid-to-win-spanish-super-cup |url-status=live }}</ref> On 31 January, a Spanish court ruled in favor of accepting Gavi's new contract with Barcelona until 2026, signed in September the previous year, despite opposition from La Liga president [[Javier Tebas]] who argued that the new deal would not fit in the club's salary limit that season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marsden |first1=Sam |last2=Llorens |first2=Moises |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/barcelona-espbarcelona/story/4865785/court-urges-laliga-to-register-gavi-deal-at-barcelona-after-initial-refusal |title=Court ruling allows Barcelona to register Gavi's new contract; LaLiga to appeal |work=ESPN |date=31 January 2023 }}</ref> On the same day, Barcelona announced that Gavi would acquire the number 6 shirt, previously worn by his coach and Barcelona legend, Xavi.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3042970/gavi-to-wear-the-number-6-jersey-for-barca |title=Gavi to wear the number 6 jersey for Barça |work=FC Barcelona |date=31 January 2023 |access-date=1 February 2023 |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512220414/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3042970/gavi-to-wear-the-number-6-jersey-for-barca |url-status=live }}</ref> On 21 March, a court ruling ordered that the new deal to be revoked as it would exceed the club's salary limit, and a return to his previous enrolment as a youth-team player with his old number 30 shirt.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marsden |first1=Sam |last2=Llorens |first2=Moises |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/barcelona-espbarcelona/story/4906913/source-barcelona-to-appeal-court-ruling-over-gavi-dispute |title=Barcelona to appeal court's decision to reverse Gavi's registration - source |work=ESPN |date=21 March 2023 |access-date=22 March 2023 |archive-date=22 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322055606/https://www.espn.com/soccer/barcelona-espbarcelona/story/4906913/source-barcelona-to-appeal-court-ruling-over-gavi-dispute |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ballús |first=Pol |title=Gavi could leave Barcelona for free after court ruling |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4331321/2023/03/21/gavi-barcelona-contract-la-liga/ |access-date=27 March 2023 |website=The Athletic |date=21 March 2023 |language=en |archive-date=24 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230424031609/https://theathletic.com/4331321/2023/03/21/gavi-barcelona-contract-la-liga/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Dear Gavi, here's why you should join [insert club name] on a free transfer |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4339266/2023/03/24/gavi-barcelona-free-transfer-summer/ |access-date=27 March 2023 |website=The Athletic |date=24 March 2023 |language=en |archive-date=1 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230401133707/https://theathletic.com/4339266/2023/03/24/gavi-barcelona-free-transfer-summer/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 20 June 2023, Barcelona managed to complete Gavi's registration to La Liga as a first-team player, subsequently extended his contract with Barcelona until June 2026, which contained a release clause of €1bn.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 June 2023 |title=Barcelona complete Gavi registration with La Liga |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/barcelona-complete-gavi-registration-with-la-liga-37708286 |access-date=22 June 2023 |website=OneFootball |language=en |archive-date=22 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230622051849/https://onefootball.com/en/news/barcelona-complete-gavi-registration-with-la-liga-37708286 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2023–present====
Having been injured since November 2023, Gavi came back to training on 12 September 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 September 2024 |title=Gavi returns to Barcelona training after ACL tear |url=https://www.espn.in/football/story/_/id/41229755/barcelona-star-gavi-returns-training-acl-injury |access-date=12 September 2024 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> After 348 days since his injury, he made his return to action on 20 October 2024 in a 5–1 victory against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]], replacing his teammate [[Pedri]] who handed him the captain's armband.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4152481/gavi-returns-after-348-days-out |title= Gavi returns after 348 days out |publisher= FC Barcelona |date=20 October 2025 }}</ref> Similarly, he also made an appearance in ''El Clásico'' as a substitute once again on 26 October 2024 where Barcelona won comfortably by 4–0 against Real Madrid in the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium|Bernabéu]]. He picked up a yellow card in the 90th minute following a clash with [[Vinícius Júnior|Vinicius Jr]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/vinicius-jr-ballon-dor-taunt-gavi-barcelona-provoke-real-madrid-winger-closing-stages-el-clasico/blt1a0f929d7b6f15cc#cs54d8f5d3fa44f937 |title=Vinicius Jr makes Ballon d'Or taunt to Gavi after Barcelona midfielder tried to provoke Real Madrid winger during closing stages of El Clasico |publisher=GOAL |date=27 October 2024 |access-date=25 February 2025 |archive-date=2 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241102180750/https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/vinicius-jr-ballon-dor-taunt-gavi-barcelona-provoke-real-madrid-winger-closing-stages-el-clasico/blt1a0f929d7b6f15cc#cs54d8f5d3fa44f937 |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal of the season against [[Athletic Bilbao]] in the [[2025 Supercopa de España|Supercopa de España]] semi final tie where he also assisted teammate [[Lamine Yamal]] in a 2–0 victory and eventually winning the cup.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4195734/athletic-club-0-2-fc-barcelona-half-the-job-done |title=Athletic Club 0-2 FC Barcelona |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=9 January 2025 |access-date=25 February 2025 |archive-date=14 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114225947/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/news/4195734/athletic-club-0-2-fc-barcelona-half-the-job-done |url-status=live }}</ref> On 31 January 2025, he extended his contract with the club until 2030.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4208572/gavi-blaugrana-until-2030 |title=Gavi, blaugrana until 2030 |publisher=FC Barcelona |date=31 January 2025 |access-date=1 February 2025 |archive-date=1 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250201043855/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4208572/gavi-blaugrana-until-2030 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Gavi featured in the first two matches of Barcelona's opening [[La Liga]] matches of the [[2025–26 FC Barcelona season|2025–26]] season as a substitute, after which suffered a [[medial meniscus]] injury to his right knee and underwent surgery in early September 2025, ruling him out for an extended period of around four to five months. He was cleared to return to the squad in mid-March, 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marsden |first=Sam |date=2026-03-14 |title=Gavi set for Barcelona return vs. Sevilla after seven-month absence |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48203764/gavi-set-barcelona-return-vs-sevilla-seven-month-absence |access-date=2026-03-15 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
Gavi has represented Spain at under-15 and under-16 level.<ref name=WF/><ref name=vavel/>

On 30 September 2021, Gavi received a surprise call-up to the senior [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]] by the manager [[Luis Enrique]]. He made his debut in their [[UEFA Nations League]] [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals|semi-final]] win against [[Italian national football team|Italy]] on 6 October, becoming the youngest player to ever represent Spain at senior level.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58820411 |title=Italy 1 Spain 2 |date=6 October 2021 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=7 October 2021 |archive-date=10 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211010135414/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58820411 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="future">{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/spain-esp/story/4493392/how-barcelonas-gavi-became-spains-present-and-future |title=How 17-year-old Gavi became Spain's present and future |publisher=ESPN |last1=Lowe |first1=Sid |date=8 October 2021 |access-date=11 October 2021 |archive-date=26 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230326051447/https://www.espn.com/soccer/spain-esp/story/4493392/how-barcelonas-gavi-became-spains-present-and-future |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Final|final]] against [[France national football team|France]] on 10 October, Spain ultimately suffered a 2–1 defeat.<ref name="2021 Nations League Final">{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=589985 |title=Spain vs. France – Football Match Report |publisher=ESPN |date=10 October 2021 |access-date=10 October 2021 |archive-date=5 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221105003859/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=589985 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 5 June 2022, he scored his first senior goal in the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League|Nations League]] away against the Czech Republic, becoming the youngest player to ever score representing Spain at senior level.<ref name="Youngest goalscorer of senior Spain national team – Gavi">{{cite web |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2640386/gavi-becomes-youngest-ever-goalscorer-for-spanish-national-side |title=Gavi becomes youngest ever goalscorer for Spanish national side |date=6 June 2022 |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=12 June 2022 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220612202223/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2640386/gavi-becomes-youngest-ever-goalscorer-for-spanish-national-side  |archive-date=12 June 2022}}</ref>

Gavi was named in Spain's squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar, in which he started in all four matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/spain-2022-world-cup-who-is-luis-enriques-26-man-squad-2022-11-14/ |title=Spain at the 2022 World Cup: who is in Luis Enrique's 26-man squad? |publisher=Reuters |date=14 November 2022 |access-date=2 December 2022}}</ref> With his goal against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] in Spain's first game of the tournament, Gavi became the third youngest player (only behind [[Pelé]] and [[Manuel Rosas (footballer, born 1912)|Manuel Rosas]]) to score in a World Cup match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theanalyst.com/eu/2022/11/youngest-players-to-score-world-cup-fifa/|title=The Youngest Players to Score at a World Cup|first=Matt|last=Furniss|date=23 November 2022|access-date=23 January 2023|website=The Analyst|archive-date=29 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230329171540/https://theanalyst.com/eu/2022/11/youngest-players-to-score-world-cup-fifa/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 15 October 2023, Gavi scored the only goal in a 1–0 away win over [[Norway national football team|Norway]] during the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|Euro 2024 qualifying]], securing his national team's qualification to the major tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro-qualifying/2024/norway-v-spain-uefa-euro-qualifying-live_sto9834703/story.shtml |title=Norway 0-1 Spain: Gavi goal seals qualification for La Roja and secures Scotland's spot at Euro 2024 |publisher=Eurosport |date=16 October 2023 |access-date=6 June 2024 |archive-date=16 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231016080858/https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro-qualifying/2024/norway-v-spain-uefa-euro-qualifying-live_sto9834703/story.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> A month later, on 19 November, he sustained an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|ACL injury]] in his right knee and a damaged meniscus during a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] match against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]], which would force him to miss both the [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024 finals]] and the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics|2024 Olympic Games]] for Spain.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sanderson |first=Tom |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2023/11/19/fc-barcelona-star-gavi-tears-acl-and-is-out-for-rest-of-season-as-reports/ |title=FC Barcelona Star Gavi Tears ACL And Is Out For Rest Of Season, AS Reports |work=Forbes |date=19 November 2023 |access-date=20 November 2023 |archive-date=20 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231120172438/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tomsanderson/2023/11/19/fc-barcelona-star-gavi-tears-acl-and-is-out-for-rest-of-season-as-reports/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Graham Hunter of [[ESPN]] hailed Gavi as a highly promising young player in 2021, comparing him to former Barcelona midfielders [[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]] and [[Andrés Iniesta]] due to his dribbling, anticipation, intelligence, vision, passing, first touch, close control, change of pace, and quick reflexes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.in/football/barcelona-espbarcelona/story/4485322/prodigious-ansu-fati-and-gavi-give-barcelona-hope-of-a-brighter-future-in-a-dismal-season |title=Ansu Fati and Gavi are Barcelona's future rising from the depths of a lost season |publisher=ESPN |last=Hunter |first=Graham |date=28 September 2021 |access-date=13 February 2022 |archive-date=13 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230213173808/https://www.espn.in/football/barcelona-espbarcelona/story/4485322/prodigious-ansu-fati-and-gavi-give-barcelona-hope-of-a-brighter-future-in-a-dismal-season |url-status=live }}</ref> Following his performance in Spain's semi-final victory over Italy in the 2021 Nations League Finals, Italian defender [[Emerson Palmieri]] described Gavi as a player who "has huge potential".<ref name="future"/>

Coach Hansi Flick has deployed Gavi in multiple midfield roles during 2025–26, leveraging his defensive work rate, pressing intensity, and technical ability to adapt to various tactical setups.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-24 |title=Barcelona is not expected to replace Pablo Gavi in the next transfer market. |url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/barcelona-is-not-expected-to-replace-pablo-gavi-in-the-next-transfer-market-41722497 |access-date=2026-01-11 |website=OneFootball |language=fr}}</ref>

